According to [[Strabo]], the '''Artabri''' (or '''Arrotrebae''')<ref>The common name to Strabo: Sir William Smith, ''Dictionary of Greek and Roman Geography'', vol. I, ''s.v.'' "Artabri".</ref> were an ancient [[Gallaecia]]n [[Celts|Celtic]] tribe,<ref>Strabo, iii.153, [[Pomponius Mela]], iii.1.9. (Smith)</ref> living in the extreme north-west of modern [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]], about [[Cabo Prior Lighthouse|Cape Nerium (Cabo Prior)]], outskirts of the city and port of [[Ferrol, Galicia|Ferrol]], where in [[Roman Empire|Roman]] times, in the 1st century BC, a fishing port existed which also trade in metals (like Silver, Gold, [[San Cibrao|Tin]] and Iron<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.42530|title=The Geography Of Strabo  Vol.2|last=Jones|first=Horace Leonard|date=1949|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=45-46}}</ref> ) as well as [[Rapa das Bestas of Sabucedo|wild horses]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.42530|title=The Geography Of Strabo  Vol.2|last=Jones|first=Horace Leonard|date=1949|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=107}}</ref>in the bay of Ferrol most likely administered from nearby Nerium (''Modern day [[O Eume|Narahio]]'' ''famous for its [[Middle Ages|medieval]] castle and [[Cabo Prior Lighthouse|cape Nerium]]''<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.42530|title=The Geography Of Strabo  Vol.2|last=Jones|first=Horace Leonard|date=1949|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=7-8}}</ref> ''modern day [[Ferrol, Galicia|Cape Prior]]'') in an area dominated by the Artabri (or Arrotrebae) <ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.42530|title=The Geography Of Strabo  Vol.2|last=Jones|first=Horace Leonard|date=1949|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=71}}</ref>[[Ferrol, Galicia|)]] giving name to the [[Ferrol, Galicia|Portus Magnus Artabrorum]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/pomponiimelaedeo00mela|title=Pomponii Melae De orbis situ libri tres, : accuratissime emendati,|last=Mela|first=Pomponius|last2=Vadianus|first2=Joachim|last3=Camers|first3=Joannes|date=1522|publisher=Basileae, : apud Andream Cratandrum|others=John Carter Brown Library|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=163}}</ref> (Form not just by the bay of Ferrol but [[Ria|the three rias]] of Ferrol, [[Betanzos]] and [[A Coruña|Corunna]]). Strabo reports several seaports among the Artabri. [[Ptolemy]]<ref>Ptolemy, ii.6.22.</ref>  places them among ''Galaeci Lucenses'' and gives their capital town as Lucus Augusti (now [[Lugo]]).

