The '''Bobrzanie''' are one of the [[Silesian tribes]] mentioned in the ''[[Prague document]]'' from the 11th century AD. The area they inhabited was located on the [[Bóbr]] river, from which they took their name.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=1Z9ItAtbJ5AC&pg=PA367&dq=Bobrzanie&hl=en&ei=lJkyTOL8JMLTnAfEut3dAw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CCkQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=Bobrzanie&f=false ''The Early Slavs: Culture and Society in Early Medieval Eastern Europe'']</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=i6A3Q1WQIroC&pg=PA84&dq=Bobrzanie&hl=en&ei=lJkyTOL8JMLTnAfEut3dAw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CC4Q6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=Bobrzanie&f=false ''The Archaeology of Early Medieval Poland'']</ref>

