The '''University Orientation Course''' ({{lang-es|Curso de Orientación Universitaria}}) or '''COU''' was an academic level taught in [[Education in Spain|Spain]], its curriculum set by the [[Ley General de Educación (España)|Education Act 1970]]. It consisted of one single annual course, equivalent to the second year of the current [[bachillerato]] system. The previous completion of the three-year ''[[Bachillerato Unificado Polivalente]]'' (''BUP'') was an admission requirement. In order to be allowed to progress to the then-compulsory Spanish University Access Tests or ''[[Selectividad]]'', an [[Academic grading in Spain|academic grade]] of 5/10 in each subject was needed.

It was equivalent to [[12th grade]] in the United States,<ref>[http://www.boe.es/aeboe/consultas/bases_datos/doc.php?id=BOE-A-1983-32004 BOLETIN OFICIAL DEL ESTADO, 1983-32004] {{Es icon}}</ref> the last year of [[sixth form]] in the United Kingdom<ref>[http://www.boe.es/aeboe/consultas/bases_datos/doc.php?id=BOE-A-1988-12860 BOLETIN OFICIAL DEL ESTADO, 1988-12860] {{Es icon}}</ref>  and the final [[International Baccalaureate]] level.

