[[File:Flag of the Lagos Colony (1886-1906).svg|thumbnail|The flag of Lagos Colony]] The '''''Government Gazette''''' was the [[government gazette]] for the British colony of [[Lagos Colony|Lagos]]. It was published between 1887 and April 1906.<ref>[http://www.crl.edu/collections/topics/official-gazettes/search?countryID=LAGOS+%28BRITISH+COLONY+AND+PROTECTORATE%29&instID=&pc=1 LAGOS (BRITISH COLONY AND PROTECTORATE)] CRL Foreign Official Gazette Database, 2014. Retrieved 22 August 2014. [https://www.webcitation.org/6S0unEUYJ?url=http://www.crl.edu/collections/topics/official-gazettes/search?countryID%3DLAGOS%20%28BRITISH%20COLONY%20AND%20PROTECTORATE%29%26instID%3D%26pc%3D1%26Submit%3Dsearch Archived here.]</ref>
It was continued by the ''[[Government Gazette of the Protectorate of Southern Nigeria]]'' after Lagos was incorporated into the already existing [[Southern Nigeria Protectorate]] in February 1906.
