'''Grancharsko horo''' ({{Lang-bg|Грънчарско хopo}}) which literally means 'Potters' ring-dance' is a [[Bulgarian dances|Bulgarian folk dance]] from Northern Bulgaria in a 9 beat meter. Each measure of 9 beats ({{music|time|9|8}}) has a pattern counted 2-3-2-2.

