The '''Joint Advisory Commission, Korea (JACK)''' was a [[United States|U.S.]] [[covert operations]] unit that participated in the [[Korean War]]. 

Operating under the direction of the [[Central Intelligence Agency]], JACK was responsible for inserting and extracting U.S.-trained Korean [[espionage|agents]] into [[North Korea]], conducting covert maritime raids along the North Korean coast, and providing escape and evasion support for downed [[U.S. Air Force|Air Force]] pilots.<ref name="historynet">{{cite web | last =Dwyer | first =John B. | authorlink = | coauthors = | title =Korean War: CIA-Sponsored Secret Naval Raids | work =From ''Military History'', Dec. 2002 | publisher =HistoryNet.com | date = | url =http://www.historynet.com/wars_conflicts/korean_war/3033621.html?page=1 | format = | doi = | accessdate = | deadurl =yes | archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20070930201105/http://www.historynet.com/wars_conflicts/korean_war/3033621.html?page=1 | archivedate =2007-09-30 | df = }}</ref>

